[R16] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'pCPwZuaDuR0Olej-uBrMog', 'user_id': 'EQEHZkLSwaaB1Q9oTjarxw', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "Cochon restaurant is nice with a friendly atmosphere. We ordered the catfish with collard greens and grits, sirloin with red potatoes with mushroom slices. Both dishes had an excellent presentation. The portions are adequate and the prices are high for the portion. The food is fresh and flavorful. The sirloin was tender, I got it medium since my past experiences with well done sirloin has ended in tough meat. I did send my plate back because they brought it out and the steak was lukewarm and the butter wasn't melted. When it returned everything was perfect. The current menu is limited with choices but definitely something that will soothe your tastebuds. The carrot cake was delicious and the portion was enough for two.", 'date': '2021-09-27 00:37:50'}
[R17] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'KC2we0dylciFjFvDOc8NJQ', 'user_id': 'HFAIrpDmmKuUBqcdFe024Q', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "We went there the other night, based on a referral from my work counterparts daughter. I had the blackened redfish and although I have an eaten a lot of redfish, this dish was not my favorite. It definitely had a fishy taste almost as if it was a couple of days old. A good piece of fish is not supposed to taste like this and it's hard to describe. But all I can say is after every bite of fish, I was cringing having another one I probably ate about 3/4 of it. I think there are better choices in town. Nice atmosphere, and a great wait staff that's the only reason why I gave it a three. I will not be back but that's just me.", 'date': '2021-10-02 16:10:46'}
[R18] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'AiwDNdQlPSaWs3FLLY5wPA', 'user_id': 'NwNS8d_1b-AEOI8fczF8dA', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'We came closer to closing time so it was obvious they were trying to get us to dine relatively quickly. The portion size was good and the flavors were also very good. Definitely recommend making a reservation prior to going!', 'date': '2021-10-04 01:46:50'}
[R19] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'ME2mV3l1B-ZlVqFJibFnQw', 'user_id': 'Rn5cFOENKou8x-LTwVqZTg', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Tried Cochon for the first time on a Friday night and not disappointed. Snagged a last-second reservation and was seated in the large back dining room. Pretty noisy with two big parties near our table, but all that faded away when the food arrived. Porterhouse was HUGE (and delicious) but I think we actually enjoyed the Mac & Cheese casserole more. Pineapple upside-down cake was a sweet end to the meal. Prices are definitely in the higher range, but hard to complain too much when the product is this good. Service was excellent.', 'date': '2021-10-14 03:21:45'}
