[R46] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': '5z69PwGmraROskt2wPdq9w', 'user_id': 'ugJkVYkoozvzHnQL5gpTNw', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 2.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'If you like fat and gristle and paying the equivalent of your monthly utility bills for a meal, knock yourself out. I'm sure it's easy to to dupe clueless tourists with this "elevated" Cajun/creole food, but if you've spent any time living in Louisiana you'd probably agree that charging $14 dollars for three slices of hoghead cheese and some stiff crackers is criminal.', 'date': '2022-01-14 03:19:47'}
