[R48] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'zdOb2lBYgoG2nxoH9gng1A', 'user_id': 'E5C8nBwWBhsfNaxH_yd6Pw', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 2.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "Order fried alligator and it was good but the chili garlic Mayo tasted just like regular Mayo. The bread was amazing!!!! I loved it and the butter but it came a little too late in my opinion. The service was average. Not going to complain but was far from impressed. As. For an entree I got the fried catfish. That was a mistake. It was so SOUR like someone had squeezed two full limes on top of a finished dish so that was all I tasted. It had zero balance and I even through it was $25+tax I couldn't eat it. I just filled up in bread instead. The greens were horseradish and again hit you straight in the nose. Horseradish and limes.... Gross. The grits were the best part but under seasoned. I mixed it with the bread butter to get it a bit better. I tried some of my friends Mac n cheese as well and thought the roux was gritty and the overall flavor could use a punch up. It was too mellow for me but everyone else loved it. 

