[R1] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'O1VGQbYca5TEIHRgwhKZ_A', 'user_id': 'fLw53CbhJ1rue3iSga_m4g', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "I visited this place with 3 others for the first time.  The restaurant itself is really nice. The menu is compact and initially I wasn't sure I was going to like it. I ordered the Woodfire Oysters, the Oyster Sandwich and the pineapple upside down cake. The Woodfire Oysters were delicious. I just wish there were more of them for the price. The Oyster sandwich was HUGE but it was also delicious. The slaw paired with it was good too. However, I wasn't a fan of the Pineapple Upside Down cake. It tasted like it was made with cornbread or some sort of grainy bread... I also like that I was able to pay and tip really easily by scanning a code on my phone.  Overall though, it was a good experience. I'd go back.", 'date': '2021-08-15 14:14:33'}
[R2] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'T5OOIoqjWJGd4Dlv-r_MQA', 'user_id': 'SlVL5EffSFURh4pHZ7jm0Q', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Delicious food. The rabbit and dumplings was perfect. Filet was well seasoned and tasty. Boudin balls were delicious too. Nice pour on cocktails. We didn't try dessert.", 'date': '2021-08-15 14:40:07'}
[R3] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'jTV6un-EhZCrBR4s8emxFg', 'user_id': 'xlxApWfsEtqw-HQkXY0irw', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 3, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 2, 'text': 'On every trip to New Orleans, we try to avoid all touristy restaurants and focus on simple, great food. Cochon has a very cute, woody vibe. The customer service is great, our waiter was very attentive without being overbearing. 

Food review: 

Complimentary bread: nice crust on top, soft underside, served with a light butter

Fried alligator: good but just not our cup of tea. If you like gator, try it out

Wood fired oysters: served with a very tasty sauce. We personally prefer thinner oysters. These were very plump 

Cracklings: best I have ever add

Sweet tea: the bomb! 

Cucumber salad: light and refreshing with a tad kick

Pork belly, shishito peppers, and Mac and cheese are MUST HAVES!', 'date': '2021-08-18 22:08:48'}
[R4] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'CIXlfdDylXbY3Y31tgQA_w', 'user_id': '-IaJesAxc4bvDkSX4-mYLQ', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Second time here from an out of town, and this should be a go to for everyone. I wish they still had their charcuterie plate option, but quality and taste is tip top!', 'date': '2021-08-19 03:48:28'}
[R5] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'JieNw9KG3-gl3sLw9go7DA', 'user_id': 'U7WUgd5HjSHcHrLYuIf4yQ', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "My boyfriend and I went here on my last night in New Orleans and I was upset he didn't take me sooner! I had the tuna steaks and he had the beef short ribs (highly recommend!) The cuts were perfect and deliciously cooked. I have a shellfish allergy and the waiter was kind enough to tick off all the things on the menu that would safe from cross contamination from shellfish! The service was excellent and the restaurant left a wonderful taste and dining experience memory of my last night in the culture-rich New Orleans", 'date': '2021-08-19 14:47:45'}
[R6] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'UPT4Ykv82NQX9YZOqoD1ZA', 'user_id': 'ejlR7akBVR4Iot0b-Aa7hQ', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 3, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "Best place we ate at in New Orleans. 

Alligator was great. Pineapple upside down cake was great. Oysters were great. Wish we had room to eat more pork. 

Good cocktail menu. Really friendly fun staff. Nice decor and cool clientele. Very reasonable priced for the quality and amount of food. 

I had been having a battle to pay for meals with my friends. The server for my table let me sneak my credit card to her well before the meal was over to make sure I could pay for it. Thanks for that!!!

Would definitely make an effort to visit again next time I'm here, and I want to try the butcher too!", 'date': '2021-08-22 01:14:14'}
[R7] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': '9A5tkrD1CDOD5sDUiG66Dg', 'user_id': 'tMMGYtJUrS1Ia21mkNGTNQ', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 3, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 2, 'text': "Unfortunately I was underwhelmed by my dining experience here. I was expecting it to be good from the high reviews but really just mediocre. They also hold a card for reservations ($25 penalty for no shows/late cancellations).

The cochon came lukewarm, the corn on top was cold. The meat was pretty tough and hard to chew. The flavor was smoky enough and decent. The corn cobs were very dill forward but also came cold and texture wise wasn't a very good corn. The kernels were soft and the corn wasn't sweet. 

The oysters were actually delicious but I'm confused as to why they plated it like this. They could have placed the oysters back in the shell. 

Overall, there are better restaurants in the area.", 'date': '2021-08-23 17:41:47'}
[R8] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'C6NXlco_U-7W8KLhtsTEdg', 'user_id': '9JNV6nDCnkMCCshum3Likw', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "This was one of my favorite meals while visiting New Orleans, so much so, that I decided to go back again just before my flight home.   They followed all COVID protocols, staff were friendly, provided great service, and food was delicious. Can't ask for much more.  My favorite dishes were the Bacon and Pork Pie, Wood-fired Oysters, and Chili Dusted Cracklin's, and Fried Boudin.  I don't drink but my friends said their drinks are solid and that their gumbo and pork neck special are must try", 'date': '2021-08-25 03:36:05'}
[R9] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'OswFqU3mpjF0Bf7QSgjNrQ', 'user_id': 'BmiVaDuhLWoi9vk_oT5ywA', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Nice leisure atmosphere, wait staff friendly and helpful, main course underwhelming for the price, the Cochon was lukewarm in center, maybe I ate too slow, bourbon flight was nice though.', 'date': '2021-09-01 21:04:23'}
[R10] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'ozXp-CYBDRpa42fGIVCtMA', 'user_id': 'YIsjc6B9HXtrL5u57DuMzw', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Best charbroiled oysters!! You can dip the bread in the sauce for a little extra. Love the smell of smoke in this restaurant. It's a must when you're in NOLA!", 'date': '2021-09-04 21:32:49'}
[R11] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'nPaQroRkT3s5lJyL4PUYig', 'user_id': 'CGRkejdGiNtvX-lhcOFUZQ', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 4, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 2, 'text': "Definitely a must for Nola! The food was very, very delicious but unfortunately the service was terrible that evening! Super slow and our server was confused and inattentive. We ordered the pig's head and obviously weren't nearly close to finishing it but wanted to pack it and bring it back for later. We waited, and waited for a good 30 minutes and we discovered they discarded it! The manager was nice enough to comp our drinks and gave us dessert to go but the server didn't even apologize nor  check on us...?

Otherwise everything else was amazing. Loved the oysters, rabbit dumplings... but next time I wouldn't order the pig's head.", 'date': '2021-09-09 19:48:38'}
[R12] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': '75zPo4hqjCH6JGY1cs30OQ', 'user_id': 'SKJpOreXKa1PRpvSKjzMng', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 3, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 2, 'text': "Cochon (not to be mistaken for Cochon Butcher next door) is a solid place to grab dinner.  The ambiance is fun.  The staff is friendly.  The food is generally tasty but not everything on the menu is a solid base hit.  And IMHO, no home runs to be had for the entrée section.

The menu changes, so I cannot say that I've drilled down on anything I love or hate at Cochon.  The menu tends to be very protein heavy, which I like.  In general, the food is seasoned well and occasionally, the cooks are too heavy handed with the salt.  

The gumbo is ok.  I usually order a bowel but it doesn't rank in my top 5 for NOLA.
I am not a fan of their boudin or cracklins.
I have liked their catfish and few cuts of meat.  
I believe I've had the rabbit and dumplings and it was solid but I doubt I would repeat.

All in all, Cochon is pretty good.  It's one of those restaurants for me that could be better and sometimes is depending on the menu.  Before I book a reservation, I will check their menu to confirm they have a few entrees that are particularly enticing.", 'date': '2021-09-09 20:32:06'}
[R13] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'rl9N4MD1sY9rQk2685WkyA', 'user_id': 'zK4R5IFl5aBqePPEd0fvxw', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 10, 'funny': 5, 'cool': 7, 'text': "We were referred to Cochon by a friend and very excited to try this place after our excursion to the WWII museum. 

We came rather early in the evening, around 5pm, and the place was about 1/5 full. By the end of the evening it was packed. 

We perused the menu and instantly went for the Wood Fired Oysters  with chili garlic butter sauce. They were amazing and something I would most certainly order again. About half way through we were offered bread - definitely make sure to ask for the bread first as that garlic butter sauce needs to sopped up with some carby goodness. 

With a changing menu, you'll find a variety of dishes at Cochon throughout the year. When we visited the menu was unfortunately slim pickings for our liking. I opted for the Cochon special while my partner choice the beef. What arrived was a rather large portion of ham steak - which was impressive. But that was really about it. Maybe I'm not a meat connoisseur to know the difference but it didn't impress me any more than a Boston Market ham steak, unfortunately. 

Service was lacking and slow. It took a good 45 minutes from ordering to receive our food. The table we received was incredibly tight and we found ourselves looking to the floor for placing items - which isn't great. 

I'd be interested to return if the menu was something to our liking, but not being from the area it'll remain to be seen if we can.", 'date': '2021-09-17 00:39:36'}
