[R21] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'stxPK96fGEDGr8QKL_aiYw', 'user_id': 'dqYOUAo-d0aQDCAuLeJybQ', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 3, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "The Alligator, the catfish, the grits, Delicious!!! I can't wait to explore the rest of the deliciousness on the menu!", 'date': '2021-10-24 21:53:25'}
[R22] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': '2WNygci7PTtX4N2CNEdhfg', 'user_id': '55cRvURLDKLEdWlNDWnBWg', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'If you go to the WW II Museum, this nearby restaurant (2 blocks away) is a must. We had lunch there and it was delicious: fried oyster & bacon sandwich (unimaginably tasty) and a green salad. Reasonably priced, good service, excellent fare.', 'date': '2021-10-31 16:59:42'}
[R23] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'iMDg7rm1lJXSWbaB8Nq1fw', 'user_id': '9bojiL6aS22i7WHG_OJQSg', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Been here multiple times over the years. With the amount of good food in NOLA, that says something. Inventive and fresh.', 'date': '2021-11-03 03:10:04'}
[R24] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'a5wQXUcAaX35bEFaIdx1Kg', 'user_id': 'EKVprGjUfvF5cimA94mxcA', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'We ordered almost every appetizer on the menu and everything was fabulous. Other people in our party ordered the red fish and they said it was great. Would definitely return here when we are in the Big Easy.  Great staff too.', 'date': '2021-11-08 17:30:26'}
[R25] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': '-HacMKGEdBKe4LnogTfZ2g', 'user_id': 'ZcK_lckXc2xJwGnU9E0jzQ', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 1, 'text': "MAN OH MAN DO I HAVE A LOT TO SAY!!! This was my 2nd time trying it and BOTH times it was phenomenal. I'll start off by saying it is slightly pricey but you honestly get what you pay for! I paid around a total of $117 (not including the tip) for this so I'm yeah lol anyways! Located in the heart area of New Orleans. 
The gumbo 5/5: The flavor is just so savory and delicious. The chicken and sausage is super tender and mind you, I am not a fan of okra but this one in particular is super soft and BARELY noticeable. The flavor is delicious and I never leave a single drop when I order! Definitely a must! 
The fried boudin 5/5: This is honestly a New Orleans staple but these are the best dang boudin balls I've ever had. The texture of the ball is so crispy but the middle is super soft. The meat and the rice are perfectly seasoned it's hard to find anything to compare it with and the Dijon mustard dip I believe they give with it adds a nice sour flavor to it.
The mac and cheese casserole 5/5: I believe it has onions in it? And I am honestly not a fan of onions but I barely even noticed it was in there! And I have some pretty strong taste buds. The macaroni is nice and soft while the top is nice and crispy and hits you with a sharp cheddar flavor. It's enough to honestly get as an entree! 
Lastly we have the smoked porterhouse 2lb pork 5/5: I didn't eat this myself although I think I could considering how delicious it was. The pork has a nice smokey flavor to it and the sauce that comes on top of it has a smokey almost faint wine taste to it? But it isn't anything crazy that takes away the taste of the pork. It really makes the pork even juicer. The pork itself reminded me of a Christmas ham. Except it was super tender and not dry at all. It felt lean honestly. I'm a person who tends to fear too much pork since it usually gives me chest pain if I eat too greasy but this was on point. I didn't even feel full afterwards because I was still down to get some beignets! 
Anyways, if you're visiting New Orleans I definitely recommend trying this place at least once, you will not regret it!", 'date': '2021-11-08 22:13:53'}
[R26] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': '9unutXmPv4y1PK8IKwuCTQ', 'user_id': 'Y_NVgxBRcII68dSuwfNHAQ', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 4, 'funny': 3, 'cool': 4, 'text': "Great food in a relaxed, modern location. Prices seem to be on the higher side by NOLA standards, but being from the Boston area, these prices are more what I am used to.

For food, I had the gumbo, fried gator, and wood-fired oysters. For drinks: the Ramblin Rose and the Elevation.

The gumbo was pleasant and well-balanced. It had good flavor and spice without overdoing it. Some of the rice felt a little undercooked, but I'm not sure if that's intentional. There was also a small bone in the gumbo (oops). 

The fried gator was a tasty dish as well. It was breaded nicely, and I liked the chili-garlic mayonnaise sauce and other garnishes.  I want to note that some pieces were a little less tender than others, but full disclosure, I'm not sure if that is the nature of gator meat.

The wood-fired oysters were solid. These were cooked oysters in a buttery and slightly spicy sauce. Not at all bad as far as cooked oysters go. 

As for the drinks:

The Ramblin Rose was light and refreshing. I could feel the alcohol within, but this drink is not at all spirit-forward. The Elevation, meanwhile, brought some of those spirits closer forward, as well as some smokey and spicy notes!

The food came out quickly, and the service was kind.", 'date': '2021-11-09 17:16:11'}
[R27] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'tpSmVHSAddmXzW1QkDpPQA', 'user_id': 'MxR8C0RvRhP08oRCK-8jSQ', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'A pleasant surprise of a place after a day at the museum; an easy five minute walk.  Great bar area in a modern atmosphere of a fine, fun dining experience.  Service was good. Braised short ribs were delicious with just a bit of spice and two potatoes with finely diced vegetables. Really good and recommended.  Mac-n-cheese was also good and had some great taste too. I wanted to do the oysters but I felt they were a little pricey on my budget. Great place. Try it!', 'date': '2021-11-12 02:00:06'}
[R28] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'OYn8aHACQH-_CRwL60Lpkg', 'user_id': 'lzwtI_taHXMGJqdpmJQW2Q', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Fantastic lunch spot. Great service and wine selection. Gumbo was incredible, squash was perfection.', 'date': '2021-11-15 17:53:44'}
[R29] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'TopR8CBj4GFhxnc28cft1A', 'user_id': 'NhKWcum4CeBioWCBacB8CA', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Making reservations is easy with the app.  Anastasia (sp?) was our server and she is very courteous.  There are so many great appetizers I had to order three!  None of them disappointed. I had the pork pie, boudin balls, and fried alligator.  The fried alligator is served with a mint garnish - excellent.  As an entree I had the rabbit & dumplings which was peppery, velvety, rustic, and filling! I enjoyed it.  It did not taste "gamey" at all.', 'date': '2021-11-16 19:57:58'}
[R30] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'gqWPrYpGlbd0vqpot83UqA', 'user_id': 'msjQaMwKihocOfqYmcF7GQ', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': '4.5 stars here. our dinner with friends on arrival in New Orleans. Highly regarded Cajun cuisine that works with local farms for a large amount of their ingredients. Menu, though not extensive, looked great before our arrival so was looking very forward to our meal. I would consider it on the pricy side, though maybe not for New Orleans. Very personable service throughout our time here. Once seated we ordered drinks and perused the menu. A bowl of delicious rolls with butter arrived shortly. Having just gotten off a plane and not being all that hungry, along with being budget conscious, we chose to order light. Wife ordered the bacon and pork pie and the cucumbers and herbs in vinegar salad. My choices were the chicken & andouille sausage gumbo along with fried alligator with chili garlic mayo. The pork pie was a bit light on flavor-lacking any discernible seasoning or bacon flavor. More bacon would add a lot. The crust was well made and it was cooked perfectly. Cucumber salad had a large amount, IMO, of red chili flakes not listed on the menu. Avoiding them was difficult but she powered through it, pronouncing it "fine". My gator was delicious, tasting very fresh and lightly breaded. But for me, as I was expecting, the chili mayo was too much for my palate. Very small bits of sauce added to the flavor but it was easy to add too much. The gumbo was the star of the show for me. Deep, rich flavor profile along with tender veggies and sausage that was flavorful without being too hot. I should really have ordered more of this.

I didn't pay as much attention to our companions' meals as I should have but I did try a bite of the wood fired gulf fish served "fishermen's" style that on our visit was redfish. Requested grilled, it had a great seasoning and was very reminiscent, IMO, of a fresh trout, though the person who ordered it compared it to halibut. I didn't think so.  Desserts were a German Chocolate Pie and an Apple Cider donut. The donut was pronounced flavorful by our fellow diners but I never tried it as I was fully involved in our pie. I will say it was not really like a pie IMO as the texture was very firm, not soft and moist like a traditional pie. It resembled to me more of a pecan pie with chocolate and coconut or a 7-layer bar for those who know what those are. Very very good. A really enjoyable meal. I'd come back again for sure.', 'date': '2021-11-24 22:59:40'}
[R31] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'ifLkZE7VXivOVeo1T0Neng', 'user_id': 'UHroi4TJ1xWEIG4SkQ1JlQ', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Sheesh.....get the damn pigs feet. Get the damn catfish. Get the damn rabbit. So damn awesime.', 'date': '2021-12-08 02:32:13'}
[R32] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'sYGGp014NW72EJLSKqxkgA', 'user_id': 'G1PcVLtWSB1tgr2VW2GWxg', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Hands down the best food in Nola. So good, went back a second night. The rabbit and dumplings has to be number 1 item, followed closely by the spare ribs. Was part of a group and we all did family style so we could taste everything. Honestly, you can't go wrong with any of the dishes.", 'date': '2021-12-09 18:45:48'}
[R33] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'Q6hamQDU5VuXHRt3jBLqzA', 'user_id': 'w3kBEVUMf4C6GkcBT4vPuQ', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "I came for lunch with a group of 8 for lunch.  The space itself was great and had a nice warm/homey feel to it.  We started off with bacon/pork pie and fried boudin. Fried boudin is a cajun meatball with rice and pork in it. Both starters were so delicious.  We were fighting over the leftovers and debated ordering more.  I had the cucumber salad.  It was nice to have that to brighten up my palate before the next course.  The entrée I had was a grilled flank steak with potatoes and mushrooms.  The steak was cooked to perfection and very tender.  The potatoes and mushrooms were a perfect addition to the steak.  My husband had the cochon of the day which was a fried pork chop.  Oh my lord!  It was soo good and I kept getting bites of his. 

The staff were very attentive and friendly.  This is a must-do in NO.  I can't wait to go back!", 'date': '2021-12-15 23:46:45'}
[R34] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'YDm1Nr-JMCbjMH9GnB9OWQ', 'user_id': '0KjqHIouprEuBr_8A9BJ_Q', 'business_id': '6a4gLLFSgr-Q6CZXDLzBGQ', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 4, 'funny': 2, 'cool': 4, 'text': "Out of all the restaurants I've tried during my week in New Orleans, Cochon was the best.  I should have gone back to try the rest of the menu.  For my drink, I got a lemonade.   It was house made and refreshing.

To start, we had beautiful warm bread rolls with butter.  They were like King's Hawaiian sweet rolls, but to the next level.  The wood fired oysters with chili garlic butter were incredible!  I've never had oysters served like this.    They came in a hexagon cast iron and you could taste how fresh the oysters were.  I should have ordered one more.  

Fried Alligator with chili garlic mayonnaise.  The alligator had a nice fried coating that was dressed with delectable mayo.  I order alligator whenever I see it on the menu and I would definitely come back for more.", 'date': '2021-12-16 01:37:26'}
