[R26] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'hWNPQx74kf7fB3Q0q6nHVA', 'user_id': 'BnoprwbCO9b-nBDqitsvQg', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': 'I went with a group of friends for Friday lunch, It took quite a while to get a drink after we sat down. Other than that, the service was good. We ordered a few appetizers for the table and i had the catch of the day special with crabmeat. It was good...not great, but good. For desert, i had the bread pudding souffle which was phenomenal. We will go back.', 'date': '2021-11-30 22:28:37'}
[R27] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'qVK5QsYf2n6AWQyfhKO4iA', 'user_id': 'Xbs5R5YZ6KYJq5-tDdpkaQ', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 2, 'cool': 2, 'text': "The first time I went here was about 5 years ago, and then I rebooked it when we were back in town last week. I really enjoyed the two cocktails I ordered and their drinks are very reasonably priced for the creativity and uniqueness they offer. The mushroom strudel was delicious, and the grits were probably among the best I've ever had. the squash salad was good too, but very overdressed. I got the apple pie for dessert which was to die for.

While the food and Service were still great, and reasonably priced, I remember the experience being nicer the first time I went. This time, we had contacted them a few times before hand and informed them we were both vegetarian. We mentioned it again when they called to confirm the reservation. They said they would keep that in mind and have enough food for both of us, but they seemed to have forgotten. There were no more things than the two already on the menu, and they didn't really seem to make an effort to accommodate individual preferences that my partner expressed. 

