[R28] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'EfhzZAb--Rkv4b7x8orjnQ', 'user_id': 'LtVDvMl8fZ4kthvwG4k7WA', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'I've been waiting to experience Commanders Palace for years, but honestly the food and service were just ok. Turtle soup and the Creole cheesecake to die for. Pecan crusted fish was ok... I've had better. Braised cabbage good but not spectacular.  Duck was prepared well. 

