[R42] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'n17Y1iZWXW1N2ZZgEQA1cA', 'user_id': 'qbifVpT7pTUreHP6O0GFoQ', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Great experience! If you want a fine dining experience while in New Orleans, then this is the place. They have a great 3 course brunch menu with lots of options and really good drinks too. The decor is nice and servers are friendly. The only two minor points for improvement is that this is advertised as a jazz brunch, but the jazz band only came to our dining room for about 10 minutes. Additionally they had run out of some options on the menu early on by 1:30pm, so that could be improved. But otherwise everything was great and it was a really food New Orleans experience', 'date': '2022-01-03 00:38:19'}
[R43] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'ZM0YncXSXAH7WYlud5pkIQ', 'user_id': 'tEq55WM9ea6Jl5-Ssb-CXw', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 2.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'The food is good. Our Uber driver told us this place is overrated, but I think the food is spot on. We had snails, crudo for appetizer, duck gumbo, and veal for entree. The souffle dessert is great and unique with a touch of liquor. The shortcake strawberry sauce is a bit too sweet for me.

The service does not match the high qualify food. It's the first time I got annoyed by service. A good service should be invisible when not needed and catering when needed, not pressuring. Either the waiters were not well trained or they didn't really care. At first, we couldn't decide what to drink, and our waiter just stood there while we were reading the drink menu. I felt quite pressured like a student being supervised by a teacher to order a drink on the spot. I should probably tell him that I needed a minute. But I was just settling down and wasn't familiar with the place to ask him to leave. And then I asked for recommendations, either the waiter really likes expensive drinks or he thinks the more expensive drink tastes better, he recommended the two most pricey drink on the menu, which didn't really fit my tastebud. Then comes the entree, without telling us there was an extra charge (or maybe he did? But we definitely didn't hear it), he suggested us to add crab meat in our dish, and we thought it was just part of the dish, so we agreed. Turns out there was an extra $20 for the crab. We might still order it if he told us the price, but we felt uncomfortable without being informed and then saw it on the bill. Another waiter didn't do our utensils properly, making me wonder if they were trained properly. They also forgot to serve our side dish, and the waiter was busy serving several tables, so it was not easy to gesture him. Last, the check. They brought the POS machine to the table and our waiter put 25% tips and asked if it is okay. It would be REALLY awkward if a customer says "no, I'd tip less. " So I bet most customers would just say "ok" and let go with it. I usually only tip 25% if the service is really impressive, but for them, if I have a choice, I'd tip much less. Overall, the service at this place feels pressuring and not professional. 

So good food, but no matching and unpleasant service. You can find good food elsewhere in the city with much better service. Won't come back.', 'date': '2022-01-03 16:22:23'}
[R44] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'FL59Het5UzsVHod7Mn6qHg', 'user_id': '7MdlyhLdYT6FdgFjfwL4OA', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Had a great meal here during our recent trip to New Orleans.  I really enjoyed the turtle soup, while my guest enjoyed the tomato bisque with crab meat.  The entrees were delicious as well, as I had the pecan crusted fish and she had the mushroom pastry dish.   The dessert we had the shortcake and it was also delicious.   D', 'date': '2022-01-07 15:12:37'}
[R45] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': '6k1fLZPDx0Q1eHsz2CJQ_g', 'user_id': 'n7EAcepbdIcv-7Lty7S1xw', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'My husband and I took my son and girlfriend for dinner. We had cocktails and apps first. I asked for the wine list for dinner from our head waiter. He was very slow in returning to get my selection and explaining their extensive list. We then got our entrees- no wine yet. Wine did not show up till we were halfway done eating. Then the check came after dessert. I was paying. The credit card machine which they brought to the table asked if I wanted the receipt emailed or printed. As I was in the process of typing my email, the waiter snatched the machine away, with my card, and left. Several minutes later he returned with my card. Then the head waiter came apologizing for what had occurred. This was just a zoo. When I pay almost $600 for a dinner I don,t expect this type of service.
