[R46] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'u8KmQSpBjhkrKByO5OOLXQ', 'user_id': 'R0UpTIyy6JPU9RBcPNkvFQ', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 9, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 6, 'text': 'I've been wanting to try Commanders Palace for decades! I finally had the chance to enjoy Sunday brunch with friends. What a treat, true New Orleans gem! My friend made this reservation almost 3 weeks ago. Plan ahead if you want to dine here. 

We were sat upstairs with views of Lafayette cemetery and oak trees (so New Orleans)! To add to the nostalgia a 3-person Jazz band came to the table for song requests. We suggested "St. James Infirmary" and they nailed it!!  The entire staff was very attentive and they pitched in to help each other with service. 

I ordered the three course brunch... romaine salad, pecan crusted fish, chocolate coconut bar. All very tasty and I didn't have to request any substitutions which is rare for me. The timing of the meal service was impeccable. And the cocktails and mocktails suggestions were just right. 

I can't wait to go back to try the dinner options.', 'date': '2022-01-09 23:15:06'}
[R47] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'vqPXIVTR0SA0i3pPltVYHA', 'user_id': 'dMKVKxIyqbb9FNKChEevxg', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'This restaurant has outstanding food. The choices are unique and delectable. This is one of my favorite places of all time. I highly recommend it.', 'date': '2022-01-13 21:31:23'}
