[R31] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'r7llQkgqoVprr66bQNiCKQ', 'user_id': '7kXUqtM3-jh9dccYbgoJfw', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Over all great experience.  Staff was outstanding and their presentation of the food was amazing. Especially when they make the bananas foster at table side. Turtle soup was fantastic and we all enjoyed our pecan crusted fish. The only dish that that was so so was the duck.  A bit salty and overall my wife did not like it. But 3/4 of us loved everything else.', 'date': '2021-12-13 14:37:06'}
[R32] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'D0zGwRuONrX096cVxRfhtA', 'user_id': 'WaD3sZbltS0v328YcUZ4kA', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 1.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'This had to be one of the most disappointing experiences I have ever had. Our server Jared was awful. At one point he was combative. He lied on the kitchen several times. The food was so disappointing. There are better restaurants in New Orleans.', 'date': '2021-12-18 19:18:47'}
[R33] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'CNpAK3_yWZh-pk5eNIBUog', 'user_id': 'kfLDszpAGU3qA9nXbu5jyw', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "We were lucky enough to get to eat at the Chef's Table. The dinner was fantastic and the kitchen show was great as well. Vincent took care of our table from start to finish. We gave Chef Meg full reign as too what to prepare for us and she did not disappoint. The best meal and restaurant experience I have ever had. If anything matches or exceeds Commander's Palace I am ready for it.", 'date': '2021-12-19 00:36:35'}
[R34] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'VfYc7BP3BgVNgKskn45I5g', 'user_id': 'JD7L3z31GmOuVsRRPyqdFQ', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 15, 'funny': 2, 'cool': 9, 'text': 'Covid hasn't slowed this place down, one bit. The best table service of any restaurant in North America, hands down.

When you come to a top-drawer restaurant, it's about the total experience. Commander's Palace, downstairs, is more for the locals. It's old-school elegant. Paneled walls. People who have been dining there for a long time. For the tourists, we almost always get the top floor, or the patio, in better weather. Both are lovely spaces.

The food is always exceptional. Even menu items that are a bit more "classic," like the Pecan Crusted Fish, are prepared with perfection. The  Shrimp & Tasso Henican was a delicious start. Turtle Soup is a house standard, with a bit of sherry drizzled in liberally, at service. Newer dishes, like Maggie's Autumn Mushroom Strudel, are experiential cuisine.

Dessert was excellent.  We shared a bread pudding soufflé.  DO order in advance, at the start of the meal. Amazingly light, totally delicious.

Cocktails are a specialty here. For one of the top restaurants in New Orleans, their very pedestrian bourbon list, with the rise of boutique limited-run brands like Wilderness Trail, or Kentucky Owl,  may be their only Achilles heel.

Your bread is like a cloud. Your water glass will always be full.  

Service? I've paid more, at other New Orleans top-shelf dining, for a lot less. It's not just that the staff here is highly professional. They're kind. They're gracious. They have a sense of humor. You can train someone to do a job. To treat what is, at 99% of restaurants, a "gig" that ranges from slinging hash, to sucking up for cash, there is nothing slapdash about Commander's Palace service. 

Another notable is that the front desk always is not only professional, but CALM. Pleasant. They set a wonderful tone for the evening.  They always make sure that they say goodbye, and invite you back, on the way out, too. 

Tucked away in the Garden District, it may be the last of the stately New Orleans restaurants to retain both its charm, and its culinary relevance.', 'date': '2021-12-22 13:38:26'}
[R35] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'xt57aOrB4eLGoRzN1NF7yQ', 'user_id': '_NNTaLAdqjCrw6G9J7XdKA', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Went here for our anniversary dinner and this restaurant is EVERYTHING! Southern charm vibes and pristine table setting. We had the famous turtle soup (it was good! But I felt a bit guilty eating it since it was turtle), the steak and beets and the pecan crusted fish. The food was delicious, the server went above and beyond for us; highly recommend!', 'date': '2021-12-22 15:31:37'}
[R36] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'Ix_ae2qyCeP-CSKtn6UU5g', 'user_id': 'hpuEgeybjdICIpoWrbeA3A', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 1, 'text': "This place was AMAZING.  I came here with my husband and his parents for their anniversary dinner, toting along our 16-month old son.  The food itself was exquisite, possibly the best meal I've had in my entire life, and the restaurant is incredibly stylish.  

However, what stood out to me most was the way they treated my son.  He's quite an active toddler with a recent OBSESSION with stairs, and he was having trouble sitting still (still as a toddler can be, anyway) and behaving himself tonight.  Not once did any staff treat us as though we were any less worthy of phenomenal service, and multiple staff went above and beyond with things like balloons, ice cream, and even showing us a little area where our son could go play to burn off some energy before we ate our meals.  Huge shout out to everyone* working tonight who made this a special experience for everyone in our party, including our sweet but rowdy toddler.

