[R1] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'LQMcVZWWBBYOxjFxS19MFg', 'user_id': 'kbZ-S4Rf7j9zHDrQIoTNPQ', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Beautiful ambience, coming fromCalifornia  to eat here is a bucket list event. Kisha, our server, was charming and guided us through the menu. The soup de jour (Cauliflower, Saffron, Brie soup) was amazing as was the crowning glory...the bread pudding SOUFFLÉ!  I normally don't eat dessert nor do I eat bread pudding ( most just dry and reeks of cinnamon). This is beautiful and luscious and has some "want more" sprinkled on it.  I think most desserts will pale in comparison, it is that good. Lovely!', 'date': '2021-10-20 22:39:25'}
[R2] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'lf-IjOfZkyLB9otbG0Vrng', 'user_id': '3q16V2FK_VhpRM61H_WYAQ', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Great meals and service is great. Little disappointed in the steak and fish dish not as good as remembere. Dessert and drinks are a hit.', 'date': '2021-10-23 18:45:04'}
[R3] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'iGdlCB-GNTJ9fRYn22YWAw', 'user_id': 'T3sCIo1iiRPCQ4rC7I9p6Q', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 1.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "TERRIBLE. We waited for 45 min to be sat AFTER our reservation. It then took forever to receive menus and no one came by to take our order after we were seated. We left. I don't know how you can find that service acceptable for such a well known restaurant. They had so many servers working, but were not on top of giving good service not apologetic for the bad service. They should be ashamed. TERRIBLE.", 'date': '2021-10-28 21:39:06'}
[R4] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': '56qe3HeNDFsyps4jCP5T2A', 'user_id': '5X4jRFhHiBS3lsI9BF76fg', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "My boyfriend has wanted to go here for two years and we decided this time around we would go. We read online about the famous three martini lunch (.25 martinis) and made reservations. 

The ambiance is classic and upscale and there is a dress code. 

Service was all around good from hostess to main dinning and assistants. The only thing we felt that could of been better, is our waiter could of checked back, after our main order was taken. 

For lunch we started with butternut squash and shrimp bisque soup and Delicatta Squash & Autumn Chicory salad. The soup was rich and deliciously creamy, the shrimp was a good twist and for the salad, the raisin sugarcane added a nice balance of sweetness to the vinaigrette. For entrees we had Maggie's Autumn Mushroom Strudel and The Double Cut Tasso Brined Pork Chop. The French pastry shell is a great compliment for the mushroom strudel, this dish has a home cooked feel to it and so very savory.  But now comes the pork chop! Just wow, perfectly done to temp and the flavors melted away in your mouth, luscious comes to mind when describing this dish. And finally for desert, we had the Creole Bread Pudding Soufflé, be sure to order this ahead of time, since it takes more time for this desert to be prepared but worth the wait.  Once it arrives, the waiter pours the whiskey cream over the soufflé, table side. The texture of the soufflé is so light and fluffy, not your typical bread pudding and yes, it is so wonderful.

We definitely will return and next time we will try dinner or the Jazz Brunch, maybe both!", 'date': '2021-10-29 22:31:27'}
[R5] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'nT2c51OC53HdcYx31zfyaw', 'user_id': 'P2VwTR-pwCZK-IAtNZzU-A', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 6, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 6, 'text': "When I was researching restaurants to try before taking a trip to New Orleans with friends, Commander's Palace was on the top of everybody's list.  When I heard from a good foodie friend of mine that they provided her with one of thee best meals she's ever had and that this was the restaurant where the famous Emeril Lagasse got his start as an executive chef, I knew I had to come to try it for myself as well.

The atmosphere here is very upscale. They have valet service, ambient lighting, and a dress code (which I'm ambivalent about; however, I do love a reason to get dressed up, especially after not having many opportunities to do so in lockdown.) In addition; the service was very attentive, and we had several servers as well as one of the Co-Proprietors, Lally Brennan checked on us throughout our meal. They really went out of their way to provide my friend and me with real southern hospitality. 

As for the food, it was superb! My three-course meal was well worth the price point. Everything was cooked to perfection. The Crispy NOLA Barbeque Bayou Frog Leg on Garlic Focaccia was a perfect starter to whet my appetite. The Café Pierre Lacquered Texas Quail Stuffed with Boudin was probably the best Quail I have ever had in my life. And please do not get me started on their Creole Bread Pudding Soufflé with Warm Whiskey Cream. I was overjoyed with excitement like a child when the waiter poured the whiskey cream over the soufflé. 

All in all, Commander's Place lived up to its expectations. I can see why it was on the top of everyone's list of restaurants in New Orleans, and now it's on the top of mine. Please make a reservation if you ever find yourself in New Orleans.", 'date': '2021-10-31 14:29:26'}
[R6] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'ZFBW6xTc04dJpU5BxbgZeg', 'user_id': 'XpfQzJnyxD8gBu3J4FwbIQ', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'A very nice place to eat. Wait staff great.  Martin was lovely Dwayne also. Jade kept track of our beverages wonderfully. You feel very special with all the attentive service. The food was great also.  The rest rooms were clean. 
