[R9] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'zmfLfznWKBTGZ0_kUP4ppw', 'user_id': 'psl7HjiM0dSVfD9UbNNILw', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 2.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'We were greeted in a warm and welcoming manner.  Our sever started off awesome however the service quickly went downhill.  We waited for 20 minutes before we ever received our menus.  Despite the fact that our neighboring table was seated at 8:15 and received their bread, water and menus prior to us.  Our wine glasses were never removed which caused a crowded table.  I had to ask her to remove the wine glasses.   When I asked her she asked me are you having wine?  Duh!  You took our wine order only 2 people at our table ordered wine.  The experience went downhill from there.', 'date': '2021-11-04 06:05:06'}
[R10] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'uyCvdUCpuGmheLSnBjKcCg', 'user_id': 'WIDh6WFxYgdrXsl21pu2Bw', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 2, 'text': "Special dinner with dear friends. Our service was first class and a model for any other restaurant in town. Wonderful start with gumbo that had a real 2-day prep time In how good it tasted. Enjoyed a filet of beef so soft, you'd swear that steer's last days were spent at a Swedish bovine spa. Butter soft potatoes, a lovely red wine to accompany. Finished with the justifiably famous bread pudding souffle...oh my goodness, so so good with whiskey sauce. An amazing dinner with Kisha taking care of us.", 'date': '2021-11-07 19:49:49'}
[R11] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'Nl-pnXOx_sg7_yR1_4X8UA', 'user_id': 'DbkOFoygQl7xj41ZJN1K-Q', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Commander's Palace ain't what it used to be. Apparently the dress code doesn't exist anymore. They were out of several items we ordered. The espresso machine was "broken" as if we we ordered ice cream from the McDonald's on Claiborne. On top of that, the service was awful. The kicker being when the waiter dropped a credit card machine on the table and had us close our own check. Very bizarre experience for a place held in such high regard.', 'date': '2021-11-08 04:46:32'}
[R12] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'R-5Tjj6RbPRJ1lZbndqNWw', 'user_id': '_pBzBgtCTN9PNUPfgPDI8A', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 4, 'funny': 2, 'cool': 3, 'text': "I have heard of Commander's Palace for as long as I've been a Food Network watcher. Emeril Lagasse used to be the chef here. I made reservations a month in advance to dine at Commander's Palace. It's definitely one of the few places in New Orleans that you would need a reservation for. We walked in and were asked for our COVID vaccination cards along with the name under the reservation. We were quickly whisked upstairs to the garden room. Our servers Duwayne and Jerryd were outstanding. 

We started with a few cocktails: Sazarac and Fuzzy Buffalo. I tried the classic Sazarac which is a typical New Orleans cocktail. It wasn't my jam so I traded my bf for his Fuzzy Buffalo. For round two, I opted for the Honey Rush, which was perfect. 

We started with the 1-1-1 soup trio: turtle soup, gumbo, and soup du jour (potato leek). The soups are amazing and you would have a hard time choosing just one. I didn't think I'd like the turtle soup but it was delicious and reminded me of a soupy chili but in a good way. The potato soup was outstanding with its depth of flavor. The gumbo was delicious and I had plenty of gumbo on this trip. 

For our entrees, I decided on the Gulf shrimp with greens while he had the pecan encrusted fish (Black drum). The shrimp were big and plump. The fish was delightful. 

For dessert, we went with the bread pudding souffle which is their specialty. This needs to be ordered in advance because it takes 20 minutes to prepare. I really wanted the Bananas Foster but it's a two-person dessert and my bf isn't a sweets person. The souffle was poufy and they poured a liquor laced cream sauce into it which gave it a boozy flavor. It was light and boozy, much like the ambiance in New Orleans. If you ever get a chance to dine here, do it. You won't regret it.", 'date': '2021-11-08 16:47:51'}
[R13] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'ogcNwUh3_uH9YfpuSA4zTw', 'user_id': 'wxpZQhwke9-99xaZQBYDcA', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "One of the must do places in NOLA. Haven't been here in many years. Had the pecan crusted trout with crabmeat, we'll executed.  Shared the bread pudding--delicious.  Service was a slow as I remembered, could be because they are struggling with staff like every mid pandemic.", 'date': '2021-11-08 19:32:42'}
[R14] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'v6XAtmCw2QuZ8y6FxTNgFg', 'user_id': '1AA8_YnrryU5jM-j0pnueQ', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "Everything, from the moment we walked in the door, was exceptional. The service was impeccable. The food was delicious. Chivalry is truly present here, and manners and true hospitality abound. If you're looking for a memorable dining experience, this is the place!", 'date': '2021-11-10 13:16:13'}
[R15] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'P4Ow8_yfcPt1VqebJlSXdg', 'user_id': '4guzb2aVQTAzCvqyChwynQ', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 7, 'funny': 4, 'cool': 5, 'text': "Everything here is great. No, I'm not kidding. Everything. That is the truth. From the moment you walk in to the live band to the cocktails this is THE ABSOLUTE BEST brunch in America. Know ahead of time you may have to make your reservation weeks, even months, in advance.", 'date': '2021-11-11 20:22:01'}
[R16] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'rTDL6aybsaZDYQNhZshZQg', 'user_id': 'Gzur0f0XMkrVxIwYJvOt2g', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Maybe an off day or something, but Dewayne made the famous jazz brunch way less enjoyable than had been long anticipated

Late to our table and dripping with a weird cringey attitude, we were off to a rough start. Kept hoping it would improve but bafflingly it got even worse. He lectured us like misbehaving children when we asked about ala carte options rather than the 3-course Prix-fix meal.  

Did you ever think that maybe 1 or 2 of our 6 diners woke up with digestive issues that were not present when we made the reservations a month ago? We didnt want to bum anyone out or cancel, so we just kept it to ourselves and decided to try to go a little smaller. A little less snide attitude and a little more understanding from would have been much appreciated. Maybe Trust that there was a reason we somehow wanted less, not more.  Please in the future consider that there might be a legit reason a customer might want a smaller meal. 

Unfortunately this was just a mockable moment for  Dewayne.  Everyone must overindulge and be decadent and not watch calories and live-a-little and other super "funny"  lines of persuasion we were unnecessarily and unfortunately subjected to.  I would have loved to spend the  morning over-eating and over-drinking, but I couldn't and the juvenile lame unfunny comments made it even worse. 

In addition to the poor main service, the assistants were kind of off too. They put the drinks in front of the wrong people, then the meals in front of the wrong people, then the desserts in front of the wrong people. At some point I thought we were being punked with some kind of pathetic practical joke. It's not like we switched seats or anything.  No one emptied our gumbos into our bowls, so it just sat there in its tin cup. And  the whole process seemed to take too long. 

Now, of course, all of these secondary mistakes would easily have been overlooked if we were having fun, but we seemed to be getting punishing  for some reason or bad day, and we were really just ready to be gone.  Instead we had the service "team" repeatedly disappear and leave dirty dishes on the table for twenty minutes at a time.  And Then the band came. They were good, but their timing.... not so much.  We already had one foot out the door.

The food itself was, however, indisputably wonderful and other servers we observed seemed much more smiley, friendly and -I hope- better.  I am therefore willing to cut some slack for a bad outing and hope DeWayne pays forward the same courtesy the next time someone deigns to ask for a smaller meal or an adjustment to the menu. Or even if he's just grumpy. This was my first time (others were repeat diners) and it was not a great first impression 

We will probably try again some other time for regular lunch or dinner and keep our fingers crossed that things have improved or gotten back to what I'm led to believe is ordinarily an excellent experience.', 'date': '2021-11-15 07:16:06'}
[R17] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'i1ia8lZFsYIdk02j46t1mQ', 'user_id': 'QfiLPx3kAj-iYe8jTmzQsg', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "The absolute best dining experience I had in New Orleans and it is not even close. This place deserves every accolade and every bit of hype they get. This needs to be a location everyone makes time for. I recommend booking a reservation in quite a long time in advance. While I got lucky and booked one for last seating (9:30pm) the day of hours before, you'll likely not be that lucky. Don't miss out on your chance of dining here. This is fine dining and you will need to follow their dress code (button up shirt required for man and jackets preferred). The atmosphere and inner design of the restaurant is brilliant and stunning. The staff is warm and welcoming and are definitely there for you to help in anyway they can. Very knowledgeable about the food and drinks as should be expected and they know how to sell you on trying even more. I believe if you are old enough and drink, try a cocktail or two (both Sazerac and Honey Rush were phenomenal), as well as an app, a soup, an entree, and dessert. You are here and you really should fully indulge. Give the turtle soup and the pecan crusted fish a try, both were some of the best food I have tried. The prices are honestly reasonable for what you get, as I have had higher bills from cheaper restaurants. Worth every dollar spent! From the atmosphere and staff to the food and drinks this is more than a restaurant it is an experience.", 'date': '2021-11-16 03:52:51'}
[R18] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'C9mqqvyVOVxPNouFUmbYPg', 'user_id': 'txQevFkYnKiNmw3m9szu-A', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "We visit Commander's at least once a year to celebrate birthdays. This restaurant is the epitome of fine dining. Perfectly timed service, decadent food and a quaint atmosphere make this a must for anyone wanting perfection. From the 25 cent martinis at lunch to the classic New Orleans dishes, this restaurant deserves a spot on everyone's calendar!!!", 'date': '2021-11-20 17:24:29'}
[R19] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'axEnnkCWlbcL7n-1bI4TFQ', 'user_id': '15VJa0OgXQCE6MuyhRp9-Q', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "This was one of the most amazing meals we've ever had. The service was impeccable and the food was delicious! The Sugarcane Lacquered South Texas Quail and the Gulf Fish Lyonnaise are highly recommended. The turtle soup was also very good. I was quite surprised at the flavor. It wasn't what I was expecting. For dessert we shared the bread pudding soufflé and strawberry shortcake and, since we were celebrating a birthday, the addition of the song and chef's hat for the birthday boy, made for quite the memorable dinner!", 'date': '2021-11-20 21:48:58'}
[R20] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'Yr72vNA3aCWKcQkoIQiBSA', 'user_id': 'tOJBR8PPC6WlH0Ssk65VUw', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Food was excellent, overall service fair. We ordered fish which was great. One standout of the evening was extremely attentive service from Tyler, which made our evening!', 'date': '2021-11-21 02:55:13'}
[R21] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'YUftIQbkgXfkFdiBfnp5DA', 'user_id': '_JXhTuNgs-cSEoqkWrIXoA', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "My wife scheduled us a dinner here for my birthday. I read a few reviews before going and somewhat knew what to expect. They surpassed my expectations. I'm not usually a big fan of fine dining places that require sport coat attire, but I'd definitely come back here. The service was excellent and the food was spot on. Everything is very well thought out and consistent with the entire meal. It was fun to just watch the presentation of the food and how it's delivered to each table. Awesome place. 5 star experience", 'date': '2021-11-21 20:08:21'}
[R22] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': '0CkEkVID86ZAbrp1leXU5A', 'user_id': '2vDHgwbOJdaNWzUIzYmwPQ', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Oh my, this place is just the gold standard of the luxury dinning experience. They hit a homerun for creating an unforgettable memory, with valet and impeccable service. I have been to at least half of the flagship New Orleans food locations, but I have yet to find any food or service that tops this. For example (and only a small sample), the food is brought out by multiple servers and placed on the table at the same time; also, if you get up to use the restroom, a server with come replace your napkin on your lap when you return. The traveling band, which requests requests, is also on point (available for the brunch). I have yet to be disappointed with anything (food, service or otherwise). Now, you will pay for this experience, as the meal might set you back 50ish a head, but there is no other location in New Orleans that you will provide you with as fond a memory. 

This is one of those few and far in between locations that I would not only recommend, but I would suggest you go out of your way to visit this place. If you are from out of town looking for a place, go here.', 'date': '2021-11-23 15:21:53'}
[R23] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'byf2CcCldSFJSOpUDRM6HQ', 'user_id': 'P2Rs-PkbAlIww15oaRm2vQ', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "We were lucky enough to get a last-minute reservation on Thanksgiving Day.  I have been hoping to eat here for years, but it never worked out for various reasons.  Very glad the Thanksgiving menu contained much of the traditional menu.  We began with appetizers.  My wife's romaine salad was possibly her favorite ever, and my crab and corn bisque was extremely flavorful.  I got the turkey and traditional sides for my entree (sentimental reasons).  Everything on the plate was well-executed.  My wife had the white shrimp and loved it.  We finished with soufflé bread puddings.  They were very good, but it might have been a slight mistake.  One of our tablemates got the parfait and it honestly made us jealous.  What a beautiful dessert!  Drinks were flavorful and strong as expected.  Our servers (Harold and team) were top-notch.  Overall Commander's lived up to the hype.  Can't wait to go back.", 'date': '2021-11-26 13:55:00'}
[R24] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'qzEf5D25V19ztW9Fu7oitA', 'user_id': 'piIljcy0fhEW6IhB1eyrFA', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "OMG!!!! I planned a birthday trip to NOLA culminating with a visit to Commander's. First of all, the hospitality was five star. I was greeted warmly and ushered to the bar to grab a drink while I waited for my table. The food exceeded every expectation. The most memorable part of the experience was a table visit from Lally Brennan. I cannot wait to visit the city again, and when I do Commander's Palace will be at the top of the list!!", 'date': '2021-11-27 02:10:37'}
