[R29] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': '4BJACrkHgO5ydzj8haqD_A', 'user_id': 'tyS-sIqi0FB4bxT9PTFE9w', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Amazing service from Alec, and the entire crew! Food was delicious! A must try when you visit New Orleans!', 'date': '2021-12-09 03:40:32'}
[R30] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'WALzNBCGkZFuP8eQ_SaotA', 'user_id': '0KjqHIouprEuBr_8A9BJ_Q', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 5, 'funny': 2, 'cool': 3, 'text': "Commander's Palace is one of those restaurants on everyone's list.  We arrived on a raining day and were seated on the second floor.  It was a little stuffy inside and the windows were fogging up.  

Service is really nice and the tables had nice white linens.  We were here for a light lunch, so we started with the Commander's Turtle soup au Sherry.  Soup is always nice on a rainy day.   It was hot, flavorful, and a great start to our meal.  

