[R29] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': '4BJACrkHgO5ydzj8haqD_A', 'user_id': 'tyS-sIqi0FB4bxT9PTFE9w', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Amazing service from Alec, and the entire crew! Food was delicious! A must try when you visit New Orleans!', 'date': '2021-12-09 03:40:32'}
[R30] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'WALzNBCGkZFuP8eQ_SaotA', 'user_id': '0KjqHIouprEuBr_8A9BJ_Q', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 5, 'funny': 2, 'cool': 3, 'text': "Commander's Palace is one of those restaurants on everyone's list.  We arrived on a raining day and were seated on the second floor.  It was a little stuffy inside and the windows were fogging up.  

Service is really nice and the tables had nice white linens.  We were here for a light lunch, so we started with the Commander's Turtle soup au Sherry.  Soup is always nice on a rainy day.   It was hot, flavorful, and a great start to our meal.  

To keep with the theme, we got the Commander's Creole Gumbo.  The slow cooked stock was nice and rich.  It was one of the better gumbos I've had.  

To finish our meal, we got the Creole Bread Pudding Souffle.  This dessert is a must.  They finish the dessert at the table and it's a crowd pleaser to share for sure.", 'date': '2021-12-10 00:20:47'}
[R31] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'r7llQkgqoVprr66bQNiCKQ', 'user_id': '7kXUqtM3-jh9dccYbgoJfw', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Over all great experience.  Staff was outstanding and their presentation of the food was amazing. Especially when they make the bananas foster at table side. Turtle soup was fantastic and we all enjoyed our pecan crusted fish. The only dish that that was so so was the duck.  A bit salty and overall my wife did not like it. But 3/4 of us loved everything else.', 'date': '2021-12-13 14:37:06'}
[R32] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'D0zGwRuONrX096cVxRfhtA', 'user_id': 'WaD3sZbltS0v328YcUZ4kA', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 1.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'This had to be one of the most disappointing experiences I have ever had. Our server Jared was awful. At one point he was combative. He lied on the kitchen several times. The food was so disappointing. There are better restaurants in New Orleans.', 'date': '2021-12-18 19:18:47'}
[R33] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'CNpAK3_yWZh-pk5eNIBUog', 'user_id': 'kfLDszpAGU3qA9nXbu5jyw', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "We were lucky enough to get to eat at the Chef's Table. The dinner was fantastic and the kitchen show was great as well. Vincent took care of our table from start to finish. We gave Chef Meg full reign as too what to prepare for us and she did not disappoint. The best meal and restaurant experience I have ever had. If anything matches or exceeds Commander's Palace I am ready for it.", 'date': '2021-12-19 00:36:35'}
[R34] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'VfYc7BP3BgVNgKskn45I5g', 'user_id': 'JD7L3z31GmOuVsRRPyqdFQ', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 15, 'funny': 2, 'cool': 9, 'text': 'Covid hasn't slowed this place down, one bit. The best table service of any restaurant in North America, hands down.

When you come to a top-drawer restaurant, it's about the total experience. Commander's Palace, downstairs, is more for the locals. It's old-school elegant. Paneled walls. People who have been dining there for a long time. For the tourists, we almost always get the top floor, or the patio, in better weather. Both are lovely spaces.

The food is always exceptional. Even menu items that are a bit more "classic," like the Pecan Crusted Fish, are prepared with perfection. The  Shrimp & Tasso Henican was a delicious start. Turtle Soup is a house standard, with a bit of sherry drizzled in liberally, at service. Newer dishes, like Maggie's Autumn Mushroom Strudel, are experiential cuisine.

Dessert was excellent.  We shared a bread pudding soufflé.  DO order in advance, at the start of the meal. Amazingly light, totally delicious.

Cocktails are a specialty here. For one of the top restaurants in New Orleans, their very pedestrian bourbon list, with the rise of boutique limited-run brands like Wilderness Trail, or Kentucky Owl,  may be their only Achilles heel.

Your bread is like a cloud. Your water glass will always be full.  

Service? I've paid more, at other New Orleans top-shelf dining, for a lot less. It's not just that the staff here is highly professional. They're kind. They're gracious. They have a sense of humor. You can train someone to do a job. To treat what is, at 99% of restaurants, a "gig" that ranges from slinging hash, to sucking up for cash, there is nothing slapdash about Commander's Palace service. 

Another notable is that the front desk always is not only professional, but CALM. Pleasant. They set a wonderful tone for the evening.  They always make sure that they say goodbye, and invite you back, on the way out, too. 

Tucked away in the Garden District, it may be the last of the stately New Orleans restaurants to retain both its charm, and its culinary relevance.', 'date': '2021-12-22 13:38:26'}
[R35] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'xt57aOrB4eLGoRzN1NF7yQ', 'user_id': '_NNTaLAdqjCrw6G9J7XdKA', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Went here for our anniversary dinner and this restaurant is EVERYTHING! Southern charm vibes and pristine table setting. We had the famous turtle soup (it was good! But I felt a bit guilty eating it since it was turtle), the steak and beets and the pecan crusted fish. The food was delicious, the server went above and beyond for us; highly recommend!', 'date': '2021-12-22 15:31:37'}
[R36] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'Ix_ae2qyCeP-CSKtn6UU5g', 'user_id': 'hpuEgeybjdICIpoWrbeA3A', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 1, 'text': "This place was AMAZING.  I came here with my husband and his parents for their anniversary dinner, toting along our 16-month old son.  The food itself was exquisite, possibly the best meal I've had in my entire life, and the restaurant is incredibly stylish.  

However, what stood out to me most was the way they treated my son.  He's quite an active toddler with a recent OBSESSION with stairs, and he was having trouble sitting still (still as a toddler can be, anyway) and behaving himself tonight.  Not once did any staff treat us as though we were any less worthy of phenomenal service, and multiple staff went above and beyond with things like balloons, ice cream, and even showing us a little area where our son could go play to burn off some energy before we ate our meals.  Huge shout out to everyone* working tonight who made this a special experience for everyone in our party, including our sweet but rowdy toddler.

*I always feel too awkward to look too long at someone's name tag (lol), but I believe Xavier and Jarryd were among the all-star servers tonight.  YOU ARE SAINTS AMONG MEN, SERIOUSLY.", 'date': '2021-12-23 03:39:58'}
[R37] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'x9o-6lUanKzQfyRZasiUbA', 'user_id': '6Y5jT0xfYBmXWkBOqwDTjw', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 0, 'text': "The service was good but the waiter seemed like he was acting in a play with his way overdone Southern accent. The food seemed a little off.The duck breast was way too fatty. Maybe that is the way it is prepared but it was unlike any other restaurant where I have had duck. I had to separate the fat from the breast meat to eat it. The strudel was way overcooked. The Commander's champagne was good. I was curious why some tables got an amuse bouche and others didn't.", 'date': '2021-12-24 15:49:59'}
[R38] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'x8Jh0lR1Is6XhcR5pV9q5Q', 'user_id': 'voVeJcHVZLRZGrd7UAslHA', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 4, 'funny': 2, 'cool': 3, 'text': "It doesn't take long to see why Commander's Palace is a New Orleans institution.  The service was completely on point, everything ran like a well oiled machine, and some of the most sinfully delicious food you'll ever eat just gets cranked out like it's nothing - when one dish was done the next dish was already ready for us.  

I had the turtle soup, the smoked duck breast, and finished with the bread pudding souffle.  My wife had the gumbo, the shrimp and greens and also ended with the bread pudding souffle.  Simply put, everything they put in front of us was outrageously good.  Eating here was a top notch dining experience that was truly memorable.", 'date': '2021-12-27 04:32:42'}
[R39] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'WMFFJYCDPtf-sMxccyqlPg', 'user_id': 'tsCAjXT2oQn-cdGamwHQ9g', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': 'Commanders fully lives up to its reputation. Eating there is a full experience and it doesnt matter what meal you go for, you will have an amazing meal and a great time. Would 1000% ordering the bananas foster; they make it at your table and tell you the history of the dish. The whole place starts smelling like caramel and bananas and the taste is just as good as the smell! The gumbo and turtle soup are other must haves, along with the bread pudding!', 'date': '2021-12-27 05:32:48'}
[R40] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': '9SIgm4W9KmrIQPcjpmBxAA', 'user_id': 'lAZP6KPG7Hr3cDFV6Cj_Lw', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'This is a second review of this restaurant, and I am a true believer in Commanders Palace now! First, nothing makes me happier as a Yelp elite reviewer than when a manager or owner comes over and greets the tables. On this particular night my party was greeted by the owner of the restaurant not once but twice as she made her way around to all of the tables in the dining room. This is a true showing of Class and Customer Service. In the midst of everything that she is responsible for as an owner she took the time to come by two times in the few hours that we were there to eat our meal that is a class act. Our waitress her name was Keisha and she was fantastic, very lovely and knowledgeable of the menu and she took really good care of us. The food was fantastic and the desserts were to die for. The matrody greeted us as if we were family returning home from a vacation which was also nice. But the evening began when we arrived and the valet outside was beyond nice and accommodating for my party. He was all smiles and I wish I knew his name because he definitely deserves recognition for having been at this location for years, I remember seeing him the last time I was in town. Service starts with the first person that we experience and for us it was the valet. Definitely recommend this restaurant and everyone who works there from the outside to the inside, enjoy!', 'date': '2022-01-02 01:35:33'}
[R41] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'G0wVKcLAQD2lfqUH34_d1Q', 'user_id': '6u49z3pjNVKs1O4rBmKXvA', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 2, 'text': "Amazing service, great food and drinks. 

Everything you would expect from one of the older restaurants in NOLA, still serving up southern cuisine with class. 
Of course, the main reason we came here was to try the turtle soup, as I'm sure many do, and we gave it a try; we actually really enjoyed it. There are shreds of meat instead of chunks, and it was sort of like gumbo consistency. Mild flavored broth and neither bland nor salty. Fun to try at least once. 

I got the duck, which was perfectly crispy but juicy, and the sauce was delicious. Our servers worked as a team all were attentive for everything we needed. Dessert was also top notch, and we sat upstairs with an outside view through their large windows. 
The ONLY knock I had is that they used cheap bright red maraschino cherries on their Manhattan, which was quite a travesty to me after everything else. Over all excellent though.", 'date': '2022-01-02 16:59:46'}
[R42] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'n17Y1iZWXW1N2ZZgEQA1cA', 'user_id': 'qbifVpT7pTUreHP6O0GFoQ', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Great experience! If you want a fine dining experience while in New Orleans, then this is the place. They have a great 3 course brunch menu with lots of options and really good drinks too. The decor is nice and servers are friendly. The only two minor points for improvement is that this is advertised as a jazz brunch, but the jazz band only came to our dining room for about 10 minutes. Additionally they had run out of some options on the menu early on by 1:30pm, so that could be improved. But otherwise everything was great and it was a really food New Orleans experience', 'date': '2022-01-03 00:38:19'}
[R43] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'ZM0YncXSXAH7WYlud5pkIQ', 'user_id': 'tEq55WM9ea6Jl5-Ssb-CXw', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 2.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'The food is good. Our Uber driver told us this place is overrated, but I think the food is spot on. We had snails, crudo for appetizer, duck gumbo, and veal for entree. The souffle dessert is great and unique with a touch of liquor. The shortcake strawberry sauce is a bit too sweet for me.

The service does not match the high qualify food. It's the first time I got annoyed by service. A good service should be invisible when not needed and catering when needed, not pressuring. Either the waiters were not well trained or they didn't really care. At first, we couldn't decide what to drink, and our waiter just stood there while we were reading the drink menu. I felt quite pressured like a student being supervised by a teacher to order a drink on the spot. I should probably tell him that I needed a minute. But I was just settling down and wasn't familiar with the place to ask him to leave. And then I asked for recommendations, either the waiter really likes expensive drinks or he thinks the more expensive drink tastes better, he recommended the two most pricey drink on the menu, which didn't really fit my tastebud. Then comes the entree, without telling us there was an extra charge (or maybe he did? But we definitely didn't hear it), he suggested us to add crab meat in our dish, and we thought it was just part of the dish, so we agreed. Turns out there was an extra $20 for the crab. We might still order it if he told us the price, but we felt uncomfortable without being informed and then saw it on the bill. Another waiter didn't do our utensils properly, making me wonder if they were trained properly. They also forgot to serve our side dish, and the waiter was busy serving several tables, so it was not easy to gesture him. Last, the check. They brought the POS machine to the table and our waiter put 25% tips and asked if it is okay. It would be REALLY awkward if a customer says "no, I'd tip less. " So I bet most customers would just say "ok" and let go with it. I usually only tip 25% if the service is really impressive, but for them, if I have a choice, I'd tip much less. Overall, the service at this place feels pressuring and not professional. 

So good food, but no matching and unpleasant service. You can find good food elsewhere in the city with much better service. Won't come back.', 'date': '2022-01-03 16:22:23'}
[R44] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'FL59Het5UzsVHod7Mn6qHg', 'user_id': '7MdlyhLdYT6FdgFjfwL4OA', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Had a great meal here during our recent trip to New Orleans.  I really enjoyed the turtle soup, while my guest enjoyed the tomato bisque with crab meat.  The entrees were delicious as well, as I had the pecan crusted fish and she had the mushroom pastry dish.   The dessert we had the shortcake and it was also delicious.   D', 'date': '2022-01-07 15:12:37'}
[R45] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': '6k1fLZPDx0Q1eHsz2CJQ_g', 'user_id': 'n7EAcepbdIcv-7Lty7S1xw', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'My husband and I took my son and girlfriend for dinner. We had cocktails and apps first. I asked for the wine list for dinner from our head waiter. He was very slow in returning to get my selection and explaining their extensive list. We then got our entrees- no wine yet. Wine did not show up till we were halfway done eating. Then the check came after dessert. I was paying. The credit card machine which they brought to the table asked if I wanted the receipt emailed or printed. As I was in the process of typing my email, the waiter snatched the machine away, with my card, and left. Several minutes later he returned with my card. Then the head waiter came apologizing for what had occurred. This was just a zoo. When I pay almost $600 for a dinner I don,t expect this type of service.
https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g60864-d426290-r824373517-Commander_s_Palace-New_Orleans_Louisiana.html#', 'date': '2022-01-09 20:22:53'}
[R46] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'u8KmQSpBjhkrKByO5OOLXQ', 'user_id': 'R0UpTIyy6JPU9RBcPNkvFQ', 'business_id': '_C7QiQQc47AOEv4PE3Kong', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 9, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 6, 'text': 'I've been wanting to try Commanders Palace for decades! I finally had the chance to enjoy Sunday brunch with friends. What a treat, true New Orleans gem! My friend made this reservation almost 3 weeks ago. Plan ahead if you want to dine here. 

We were sat upstairs with views of Lafayette cemetery and oak trees (so New Orleans)! To add to the nostalgia a 3-person Jazz band came to the table for song requests. We suggested "St. James Infirmary" and they nailed it!!  The entire staff was very attentive and they pitched in to help each other with service. 

