[R2] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': '4p_tQeWQfVamd9HLoyVxtA', 'user_id': 'Y3opWVfXxR6AoG0RBHl0fA', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Food was good but the bartender on the third floor on New Year's Day was rude. I wanted to get an appetizer as my entree and she would not let me do that. I was told that I had to get a side if I wanted to get the gator bites as my main dish. Me and my girlfriend ordered the seafood pasta, a hurricane, spinach dip, and the gator bites and was told that was not enough and had to order a side with the gator bites. I don't like being told what to order.", 'date': '2022-01-03 18:36:44'}
[R3] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'ixyEKsDYDSXQLvrKX6J96A', 'user_id': '80AAoEHuS-R1iKzDAd4qqQ', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Long line and food was ok. Definitely doesn't live up to the hype. If you're on bourbon street, it's late, and you're hungry then sure settle for Oceana grill other than that I'd recommend finding other eateries NOLA has to offer", 'date': '2022-01-04 19:47:06'}
[R4] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'mfGblxA0SOlLH5hIfqpjdQ', 'user_id': 'VLsPCWn5j2tKUXiJvHJ1og', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "I would just rate this restaurant okay. I have eaten much better seafood, not sure how it is rated so high. We ate a late lunch here around 2:30 and I am not sure if that was the cause and the food wasn't fresh. My husband and I shared the seafood platter and my son had a burger. He said the burger was good. The oysters on the platter were fried well and the shrimp were pretty good. The catfish was dry and chewy. The French fries were cold and hard. Hush puppies had a good flavor but were dense. Service was good. I would try somewhere different if I wanted to eat seafood again.", 'date': '2022-01-04 22:38:36'}
[R5] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'gxmWLrFT9RqbLPO9hHc4xA', 'user_id': 'xjRtish2aXdJsVdsDZjBkw', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Food: The food was incredible. The absolute best item was the bread pudding. I'll definitely keep going back to get it. It was sensational. The oysters with the sauce were incredible. I didn't love the beans from the taste of New Orleans but the other two dishes were good. The crab cakes were very salty but the rice was amazing. The gator bites were also really good.

Vibe: The vibe of the venue and the staff was absolutely incredible. They were super fast and friendly and helpful. I forgot my phone and the waiter chased me in the street to hand it back. Absolutely wonderful and would definitely keep going back.", 'date': '2022-01-04 22:49:29'}
[R6] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'cfT3eH0RDfpItqS9CUrKLA', 'user_id': 'KWxvkl4rONoJCSLr1n51_w', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 4, 'funny': 2, 'cool': 3, 'text': 'The hotel I'm staying at suggested Oceana for breakfast or lunch and it has tons of great reviews, so naturally it's where I wandered into for brunch this morning. It's tucked right around the corner from Bourbon street so it's in a main area, although parking really stinks in French Quarter so good luck finding a spot.

Anyway, I really wanted some shrimp and grits and they have one that's made with their signature New Orleans BBQ sauce. Oh my goodness. The waitress (Tasha) came by to check up on us and when she asked me how it was I just looked back up at her with a "this is heavenly" face. FYI it's not your typical bbq sauce but it's made with garlic and spices and it's both sweet and salty. Some umami in there for sure. Yum. I can't even describe what this tasted like so you'll just have to order it for yourself. The shrimp were pretty big and all of this greatness was placed atop a massive portion of perfect creamy grits.

They have a huge selection of food and plenty of seating. I will definitely be back on my next trip to NOLA!', 'date': '2022-01-04 23:43:32'}
[R7] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'NuojIAA2AmPR_OUop6DA7g', 'user_id': 'v24RjY1EMIqUXXoFbeYZXA', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 0, 'text': "This is a cool restaurant located off of Bourbon Street. There was little to no wait time at the door. Just make sure to tell the hostess that you are on the VIP list . There really isn't any parking so you will most likely have to walk. 

We ordered the Mardi Gras pasta, crab cakes,
oysters, and seafood gumbo. The highlight would have to be the crab cakes. Probably the best crab cakes I've had in some time. The gumbo was ok but could have used a little more Cajun flavor and seafood. The oysters were good but also nothing spectacular. 

They have a few drinks on the menu and we ordered the daiquiris. The competition is high so I probably wouldn't stop here again (unless I'm hungry for some crab cakes), however our waiter was very nice and we enjoyed the service.", 'date': '2022-01-05 03:48:14'}
[R8] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'tjFb9fETw_q5irQwXkx6aw', 'user_id': 'OmBdxW1NM_qAnrUDfx16gw', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': "Whooo! Our first stop while visiting NOLA! My bf and I arrived to Louisiana late evening on a Monday and we found this spot on yelp to check out on our foodie trip! We ordered a couple items off the menu: fried seafood platter with shrimp and catfish plus fries, gumbo, and half fried/half grilled gator bites. 
Pros: Service was excellent for us, shoutout to our server of the night (Justin)!He was exceptional and made our first trip to New Orleans such a great one. Food is affordable and we shared almost everything! Would recommend for late night eats in the French Quarter if you're visiting.", 'date': '2022-01-06 02:20:05'}
[R9] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'iRw7k19uAleHGBQ3UG6q4Q', 'user_id': 'FsvZpP9m3RG95EvjDE5JWQ', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Landed in NOLA really late and was looking for a place walking distance from my hotel that would be open at midnight. This popped up on my search and being a pescatarian, I was ecstatic. It surprisingly wasn't crowded and I got seated relatively quickly. The service was incredible and my server was such a sweetheart. Checked in often and was really warm and welcoming (got that southern hospitality immediately upon arrival to Louisiana). I ordered the shrimp platter and it came out really fast. The portion is VERY generous and I got through 3/4 of it. I was a little underwhelmed by the flavor because it basically tasted like frozen shrimp and fries I get at the local market and defrost. It wasn't bad (minus the tartar sauce which did taste funny/old) but it wasn't something phenomenal. The hush puppies were actually pretty good--had a kick to them. All in all, a decent spot to visit for a quick bite. My tour guide recommended it to our group a few days later and suggested the blackened rockfish and had I stayed longer I would've gone back and tried it because it was a nice spot. Definitely recommend and would visit again on my next trip.", 'date': '2022-01-06 08:00:03'}
[R10] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'qw-rNcNbldT7iOlmQO1rUQ', 'user_id': 'hz41UvZC2pIas9am0yhASQ', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Food was delicious! We had the Mardi Gras Pasta as well as the entree special of the day which was crab cakes and shrimp. Both were delicious. Our waiter Carlton was excellent. Always on top of everything and made it a great dining experience.', 'date': '2022-01-07 01:51:23'}
[R11] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'EW788vnFjG5l8CDte_dKtQ', 'user_id': '7MdlyhLdYT6FdgFjfwL4OA', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Pleasant surprise.  We were looking for breakfast on our last day there and stopped in since it was close to the hotel.   Saw the crab cakes and had to try them (despite wanting breakfast).   They were delicious.   We love crab cakes and they were some of the best we've had.  She had a veggie omelette that was topped with an amazing sauce.   I had the New Orleans style French toast that was also delicious.   Happy with our unplanned visit.  Would go again.", 'date': '2022-01-07 15:15:20'}
[R12] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'JL8_QjarAtmp1rDLf_FlIQ', 'user_id': '6gs1bGaQIAn5PzZ97qpfPw', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Our family came to New Orleans as a stop on a cross country road trip. My first time in New Orleans and my parents 2nd (in over 20 years). We had dogs and had a little trouble finding a place that would allow us to have our dogs. We found Oceana and stopped in to check that we would be good, though they had closed their patio today they accommodated kindly for us with ease and we had a whole patio to ourselves. Errol was our server and was kind, courteous and gave great service. My mom and I shared the Crawfish Étouffe and The Barbecue Shrimp! Both were great but the shrimp dish was to die for! Errol also recommended the Golden Cadillac Margaritas which has a cube of dry ice that makes the drink bubble. Overall great experience and would highly recommend!', 'date': '2022-01-08 00:45:48'}
[R13] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'V6nN2q8I5XOWXcaYqZRU7Q', 'user_id': 'TN1sy59q0SIxTLL-WqTV_w', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 1.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Hmmm....I was not impressed. First, I have to start with, upon arriving I checked-in, using Yelp; that earned me a 10% discount on my bill. It said to show it to the waitress or Manager.  I did that and here is how the convo went.
Me: I have a 10% off coupon for checking in on Yelp. (And I showed her my phone and she read that it said that)
Her: Oh, you have to print that put
Me: Uhh, it doesn't say that at all, and how do you expect me to print something while I'm seated in a restaurant 
Her: I know, it doesn't make sense, but we've been getting lots of those, and the Manager said it must be printed
Me: It doesn't say any of what you just said; it says to show you
Her: I know, I'm sorry

I let it go. 10% isn't much, but still, why false advertise?  That set the mood for the rest of the dinner.  Waitress disappeared for lengthy periods of time. They brought the wrong order, COLD, to one of my party members.  Oh, we were a party of 6. They brought 1 dish out, 15 mins before everyone else's (it wasn't an appetizer). When they brought the rest, they forgot 1 entire dish. Another 10-minute wait for that. Then 5 mins later they bring me my dish...again.  I told the guy (which wasn't my waitress) he might as well leave it since it was made, just don't charge me, this earned a laugh. I got the catfish platter. I kid you not, there was nothing "flaky" or "fried" about it.  What I got was soggy breaded pieces of fish. I'm sure it had been sitting under the heat lamp for some time. We asked for more tarter sauce. It took, literally 10 minutes to get it. We saw the waitress pass by, and she said, and I quote, "They had to go up to the freezer to get it. It should be here soon."  You get the idea.  Fast forward, check time. Party of 6, split in 2, guess what?  You can guess,  wrong dishes on the check, stuff we didn't even order on the check.  Total visit time 2 hrs for a party of 6 and it wasn't because of us or them being super busy.

I WOULD NOT RECOMMEND THIS PLACE!', 'date': '2022-01-08 14:59:38'}
[R14] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'a3KiN3JzDC9trp9WDvM3xQ', 'user_id': 'Me2o8pvpo4x8-zX60N-zuw', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'We had some of the most delicious food at this location! We got Grilled Alligator bites, Oysters, Mardi Gras Pasta,  and a sampler called "The Taste of New Orleans." Everything was seasoned and cooked to perfection! This was one of the best restaurants in New Orleans we've tried. And our server Latricia was amazing! She was fast, efficient, and always checked up on us. Not to mention her great personality and recommendations. She definitely attributed to our visit! If my best friend and I are ever in New Orleans, we will definitely return!', 'date': '2022-01-08 17:58:02'}
[R15] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'QLQZ06Z_TqYeGjmozwf4OQ', 'user_id': 'OoF6I7xincHA9NKk5d3vkw', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Delicious Cajun creole food in the French quarter. Good food here and it never disappoints! Delicious desert also!', 'date': '2022-01-08 21:19:02'}
[R16] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'IIFRWX9pq9QdYcg58ioC2Q', 'user_id': '1xIjREP_LWSTjxOTdWZDUg', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 2, 'funny': 1, 'cool': 2, 'text': "Came here on the recommendation of our tour guide and boy was I glad that I did!  They have an extensive menu of many creole and cajun favorites, but it was no contest for me, from the moment the tour guide mentioned his favorite dish, the blackened redfish etouffee I knew that was the dish for me.    Wow!  This dish was spicy and flavorful, a perfect combination of the spicy blackened redfish and the creamy crawfish etouffee.  

It also came with jambalaya which was also packed with flavor and was very tasty.  The sauteed mustard greens were surprisingly enjoyable as well.  I only didn't finish them because I was stuffed and of all of the parts of the meal was the least impressive, but don't let that fool you, they were a great veggie side! 

The place has a great vibe, and like many spots in New Orleans, a hidden outdoor patio in the courtyard inside.  While the weather was nice enough for us to enjoy the outdoors, their busyness did not allow for it on this trip.  We went on a weekend at lunch, and there was a decent line to get in and get a table so plan accordingly especially if you are a bigger group.  

The staff was super friendly and personable.  We were in town for the Bills game and were still wearing our Bills gear after a fun win on Thanskgiving, the staff were happy to chat about the Bills and the game in a fun and friendly way.  

Definitely a spot I would look to visit again when in town!  Try Oceana for a great selection of cajun and creole favorites!", 'date': '2022-01-08 21:38:50'}
