[R19] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'pt4iJ9rIxA-inJYPULlr3g', 'user_id': 'tiFCgiZyfSiekjWBqmNJkQ', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Damon was a great server and the ultimate Bloody Mary was an experience!!!', 'date': '2022-01-09 03:47:13'}
[R20] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'fPp6XpZ-XvTX4WNLKmi14g', 'user_id': 'ogewDtUupSSDzwIpSHFi_A', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 1.0, 'useful': 1, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Absolutely trash. I don't understand how this place is so highly rated. The only thing I was impressed with was our waiter. He made our unpleasant experience bearable. 

My daughter ordered shrimp pasta and was brought chicken pasta which she sent back. The chicken pasta was chicken fingers cut up in strips and placed in pasta. Our waiter offered to replace it with the correct item and my daughter declined. 

My charbroiled oysters were cold. They tasted like the oysters were raw, they placed the topping in the microwave and then put them on top of the oysters. 

My sausage in the Taste of New Orleans was good but they could've kept the rest of it. 

My little one enjoyed her chicken fingers and fries. 

Throughout our meal the waiter came back and checked on us. I hardly touch the oysters and only ate the sausage from the taste of New Orleans. With each item I gave back he became concerned and offered to replace the items which we declined. He went to get the manager. 

Manger came over and was defensive. He asked what the problem was and let him know we didn't like the food. His response was what would you like for me to do with all this food. I was in disbelief. I responded I didn't ask for you to come to the table. Our waiter was trying to make our visit right. I didn't ask u to comp anything on our check. He replied I'll try and discount something. 

They actually wanted me to pay for the chicken pasta that should've been shrimp pasta. The manger discount was taking off the chicken pasta. He didn't honor the Yelp 10% discount offer for checking in. He said he couldn't offer any more discount than he already has. 

I get asked from folks all the time what spots to check out while in New Orleans. Oceana will definitely not be on that list.", 'date': '2022-01-10 00:02:29'}
[R21] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': '8Fao_7toZ_pBwgyKrpadBQ', 'user_id': 'm41lj0VZYe2_C9pCY-jqSw', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Very good!  Great service.  Justin was our sever and he was very attentive and had great suggestions.  I had the crab cakes and they were very good - moist and plump with a delicious mushroom crab sauce on them.  My husband had the taste of New Orleans platter which had jambalaya, gumbo and red beans and rice.  He really enjoyed it.  We started with the gator tail appetizer with both fried and blackened pieces.  It was good too.', 'date': '2022-01-10 00:52:42'}
[R22] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': '7sMe8233oazAfm6DxEEYOg', 'user_id': 'UqjgDpk7uiTKPADEf0nJZg', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "We came in tonight (two couples) and sat outside. Errol was our server and we had a FANTASTIC time. He had a trainee with him and she was wonderful as well. They suggested the Cadillac Margarita and the crab cakes and of course we got both. We also ordered the fries as an appetizer and they were all great. For our entrees I hit the Mardi Gras pasta and Errol suggested a blackened fish on top of jambalaya with fried crawfish and some sauce and it was fantastic! Over all it was such a great experience. The host at the front door was also a gem, she was super cool. We really enjoyed our dinner and the experience we had. Thank y'all for such a great birthday dinner!", 'date': '2022-01-10 03:50:02'}
