[R25] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 't3_9vtlvXznLc53bZSk7lw', 'user_id': 'r23myyXIKH683VOoo5gDxA', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Let me start by saying that everyone from the hostess  to the waiter were amazing, I just wish the food was as great as the staff. The Gumbo was lacking in substance and flavor.  The jambalaya was could and the rice was over cooked and mushy. The Red Beans were Amazing! The cocktail was fun but weak.', 'date': '2022-01-12 06:31:38'}
[R26] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'ykzjlRG9a3ZwbedKi6CrMA', 'user_id': 'OAwukZOPA4_BYpGY4uBNnw', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "This place is delicious! Servers are extremely polite, helpful, and attentive. I tried their redfish plate and the sauce is so good! Blackened chicken was flavorful. Cajun fries are also so good, recommend getting that for the table! It's definitely a pricey place though so don't be surprised. Just my plate and a beer we're about $30 but what can you expect, it's seafood and delicious!", 'date': '2022-01-13 16:51:59'}
[R27] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'pzJvypqo3h5p1l7aNQFKFQ', 'user_id': 'KnpapmrTcvXhq_Sl_FmkMA', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'I decided to order the Blackened Chicken Platter and it did not disappoint. The chicken was very juicy and flavorful with the perfect amount of kick. The side of garlic mashed potatoes was also very good. Would definitely recommend.', 'date': '2022-01-13 16:55:00'}
[R28] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'UzRlGBmEOB9QJFCCWoCN1g', 'user_id': 'bQG-CTpR59NCUdKqZn1zHQ', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "We chose Oceana Grill at first because it was one of the few restaurants open after 10 PM on a weekday but ended up coming back another time. We ordered to-go both times, and our food was always ready fast and packaged well to avoid any leakage during transportation. 

Thoughts on the following:
- Barbecued Shrimp ($25): The BBQ shrimp is a NOLA classic you have to try, though I would say the name is a bit misleading. It didn't taste anything like traditional barbecue. Instead, it had more of an alcoholic/ cooking wine taste to it. It also was buttery, and tangy. I really enjoyed the shrimp.

- Cajun Jambalaya Pasta ($23): This was absolutely life-changing and hands down the best pasta I've ever had. The flavor of this pasta was so unique and it's something I had never tasted before. The fettuccine pasta was tossed in a creamy creole sauce and had bits of alligator and shrimp in it. It was colorful, well-seasoned, and just flawless. Though creamy and flavorful, the pasta didn't feel too heavy. I feel like people don't think about ordering pasta in New Orleans, or at least I certainly did not, but you have to give this a try. 

- Crawfish Etouffée ($18): the etouffee is a stew with a ball of rice in it and it's topped with bits of crawfish. Winter is not crawfish season, so I was glad to try a bit through the etouffee. Again, the seasoning for anything cajun is just so on point. 

- Fried Soft Shell Crab ($8): Gotta have crabs when you're in New Orleans but I actually struggled to find places with fried soft shell crabs. Fortunately, Oceana had it. I just wanted a taste, so I ordered one crab. It came with a cocktail dipping sauce. The crab was so good and had a texture comparable to shrimp tempura. 

I had Oceana Grill on my first night in New Orleans and it was a great start to the trip. All these flavors were so new to me and worked so well with every dish. My only complaint is that when you order take-out they give you something like Hawaiian bread instead of toasted baguette slices. Other than that, I loved all the food here and highly recommend it. 

Tips and Notes:
- If you order pickup online through their website, there is a slight discount for first-time users. Not sure if this is an ongoing thing, but something to keep in mind. 
- Most of the regular dishes had appetizer/ smaller sized dishes for you to taste and try. So, if you're overwhelmed and don't know what to get, you can get tons of mini dishes.", 'date': '2022-01-13 18:26:47'}
