[R34] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'iswBWYuD0Qnd06tub7Koxg', 'user_id': '1avBfWUqoTi4TzCwrAPQFQ', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 4.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Ok so super late and I mean LATE post but better late than never.  Honestly I've been bragging and salivating about the next time I'm in New Orleans and how quickly I will be stopping in here!  So I when I was here about 4.5 years ago our concierge recommended this place.  He also stated the best time to go before the crowds.  Basically right before HH!  Why am I obsessed with this place? Let me tell you when I say there's a crowd that lines up to get in.  To me ... it's all about the gator bites!  Best thing ever especially the blackened.  Our first visit yes (we went more that once ... seriously that good) we got the fried/blackened! The other two times just blackened! 
I was super excited at the thought of my potentially traveling to NO next month for work but with the Omnicron spreading like wildfire the trip sadly isn't likely to happen.  Obviously this would been a must have stop for me.  Til next time Oceana!  Please don't take them off the menu and if you ever get into shipping them ... lmk I will certainly be ordering!", 'date': '2022-01-14 21:26:20'}
[R35] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': '9ZhXr3u3jH0R4ULKD4l5_g', 'user_id': '4bn5d1AZYTtYQAB1eJ7yNA', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Holy moly! Everything we had was ridiculously delicious. We had the gator bites, the Taste of New Orleans and Hurricanes. I was in heaven. Not to mention Errol was such an sweet server. What an amazing, authentic experience. Def recommended everyone try this spot.', 'date': '2022-01-15 00:56:22'}
[R36] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'VESokj0f7AnQdTmTPS3c8Q', 'user_id': 'E3e7kB-ZhiiX2RIF2zolYw', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "In town for the weekend and came across this place! Wow the crab cakes are OUT OF THIS WORLD! Our server Errol was THE MAN and gave us great food suggestions! You won't be disappointed!", 'date': '2022-01-15 01:01:05'}
[R37] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'dQf3uKdpDn6Y-6mjQ-qJww', 'user_id': 'P69NKTZf19mKhpY4usda8w', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Great food and spectacular customer service I particularly drive there just to have spinach ravioli and blackened chicken it's my FAVORITE dish on the menu", 'date': '2022-01-15 12:28:12'}
[R38] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'Jsu9WFDa7YaUatuEZaJWWg', 'user_id': 'ANQdxRisQhOxyQQ2lwiIeg', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'When a restaurant is packed for Saturday lunch in the French Quarter you know this is the place to go.  How many restaurants are in NOLA?  Hundreds?? I had the chef special, Red fish.  Very fresh and tasty.  My waitress Latricia was wonderful and really worked hard,  I shall return.', 'date': '2022-01-15 20:01:36'}
[R39] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'xUyh1dSl8429iLr0B4WZlA', 'user_id': 'wki0Cdk4rRjAoJ3m7YsxSA', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'We decided to eat lunch/dinner here and so glad w did. It was actually recommended by the door staff here at the Omni Hotel. Our server T was great! I had the Taste of New Orleans (so yummy) and a bowl of Seafood Gumbo (so yummy and simple). Totally recommend this spot! Great vibe and building too.', 'date': '2022-01-15 20:42:15'}
[R40] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': '_tbtpWfFfHKFC2Vr2Hkvyg', 'user_id': 'oZi5HNU75S6k5x5mggHECA', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 1, 'text': 'It was my boyfriend and my first time in New Orleans, celebrating accomplishments of 2021 and celebrating a new year of adventures. My brother and his girlfriend recommended we try this place while in NOLA. I am so happy I was able to oblige. The Oceana Oysters and a side of fries were definitely the highlights of our order. It was so good! Corey, our server, was so hospitable! He added to my great evening with his positivity. Thank you for making our first evening in NOLA great!', 'date': '2022-01-16 05:32:00'}
[R41] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'ONywiATwq-36QjYgJC_uKA', 'user_id': 'jjsS1hJ9aHf09jbimnuuzA', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "Service was great! Atmosphere was good, we ordered the crab cakes to start and they were really good! For our entrees we ordered the Taste of New Orleans, which came out almost cold, like yesterdays food reheated in a microwave. Did not taste fresh at all. We also had the blackened Bayou Duck, which was good nothing over the top spectacular but good. It came with a side of jambalaya that was also cold and not fresh. Overall it was an okay spot, but we wouldn't visit again.", 'date': '2022-01-16 15:16:20'}
[R42] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'ggGN7NVC8f8-qT7pANVIUQ', 'user_id': 'RK7X63jsSCjdH_WudvuuhQ', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 5.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': 'Great food, excellent service.

We were in New Orleans on a Sunday evening (cruise was next day).  Went walking up Bourbon, looking at restaurants.  Many were 1/4 full or less (it was a Sunday night after all).  But this one was mostly full.  Always a good sign.

Had Justin as our server.  Excellent service.  Very attentive, but not overbearing.  One of our entrees was cold when it was brought to the table, Justin immediately took it back, and had a new one made.  Mistakes happen, it is how you handle them that makes the difference, and Justin handled it perfectly.  Of course this also speaks for the restaurant as a whole, that servers are allowed to make such a decision.  Great all around.

The food was excellent.  Had the Taste of New Orleans, and crab cakes between the two of us.  Both were excellent.  Also had the alligator bites for appetizer, also excellent, and not just one or two tiny pieces (like so many places do), but an actual decent amount.  The alligator bites would actually be enough for a small meal if one was not very hungry.

Only negative - hot sauce.  They had a couple of standards on the table, and Justin said he could have gotten Tabasco,  but none of those are very hot.   I suggest that the restaurant get some real hot sauces (this is New Orleans right???).', 'date': '2022-01-16 17:49:48'}
[R43] {'_type': 'review', 'review_id': 'pYWGh05y84O7BwzMkL2S8g', 'user_id': '2FThL9VtdO9lsaThpzi4wQ', 'business_id': 'ac1AeYqs8Z4_e2X5M3if2A', 'stars': 3.0, 'useful': 0, 'funny': 0, 'cool': 0, 'text': "This used to be one of our favorite places after we discovered it when we first moved down here. Tonight we came back and they've removed the tuna options from the menu. Super disappointed. We still like the blackened gator bite appetizer but without our favorite options on the menu, driving down here and paying for parking just aren't worth it. 

Since there wasn't tuna today we ended up with a the red fish under chefs specials. It was ok but not amazing. I really dislike their mixed veggie side as it's not the typical carrot, broccoli, cauliflower mix. The mashed potatoes are really good though.", 'date': '2022-01-17 01:40:11'}
